==English==

===Etymology===
Anglo-Norman, from Old Northern French ''[[wage]]'', a northern variant of Old French ''[[gauge]]'', [[gage]], from Old Franconian ''*waddi'' (cognate with Old English ''[[wedd]]''), from Germanic ''*wadja''.

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|/weɪʤ/}}
* {{audio|en-us-wage.ogg|Audio (US)}}

*: {{rhymes|eɪdʒ}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# an amount of money paid to a worker for a specified quantity of [[Wikipedia:Labour (economics)|work]], usually expressed on an hourly basis.

